"Gardener's Notes

Although sponges are still considered plants by scholars, I have evidence that at least this specimen is closer to an animal and still very alive. After being kept dry for several weeks, it reacts quite intensely to any water contact. Provided with enough liquid, it can soak up several pints in a matter of seconds. Apparently, its reactions vary on the quality of water, as well. When I put it into a bucket with soap water it almost completely repelled the liquid. I wish I had some holy water; I'd love to see the sponge's reaction.
I have to go back to the seashore one day and search for more specimens."